# BLASTing batch script

This script takes a series of candidate genes, BLAST them against a local 
database (eg, transcriptome from an organism) to extract relevant sequences, 
BLAST these sequences against GenBank, and retrieve results for analysis.

## Arguments

`-c, --candidates` -- Folder with `.fasta` or `.gb` files of candidate genes. 
One gene per file.

`-d, --database` -- Local database with new data (eg, transcriptome). If in 
`FASTA` format it will be converted to a database `BLAST+` can understand using
`makeblastdb` command, example: `makeblastdb -in bugula.fasta -parse_seqids -dbtype nucl`

`-b, --local-blasts` -- Folder where local BLAST results will be written.

`-g, --genbank-blasts` -- Folder where GenBank BLAST results will be written.

TODO: parameters for BLAST analysis.

## Algorithm

- Check the local database and convert if needed.

- Read folder with candidate genes and standardize file formats (ie, convert 
  `.fasta` files to `.gb`).

- Generate list of candidate genes.

- Call BLASTn command for each candidate.

- Trim BLAST results.

- BLAST results agains GenBank.
